name: David deWilde
desc: deWilde is a San Francisco real estate investor. He used to work as a lawyer on Wall Street. His wife, Katherine August-deWilde, is the vice chair of First Republic Bank.

name: Christopher Redlich
desc: Redlich was chairman of Embarcadero Systems Corp, a computer systems company. He was later chair of non-profit Healing Healthcare before retiring in 2020.

name: John C. Atwater
desc: Atwater is the founder and CEO of Prime Group, a property management company with billions of dollars of real estate assets across the USA.

name: Louise Muhlfeld
desc: Muhlfeld has worked as an HR executive and trustee for multiple prep schools.

name: Robert Reniers
desc: Robert Reiners was a partner at Sun Pacific, a company that grows, packages, and ships fruit. The company owns and operates land across California.

name: Steven Merrill
desc: Merrill is an investment banker at Merco Ventures. He sits on a number of charitable boards and trusts around San Francisco.

name: Michael Moritz
desc: Moritz is a billionaire and partner at venture capital firm Sequoia Capital. He has donated to the Lincoln Project, the anti-Trump Republican PAC. A former journalist, he set up the San Francisco Standard with a $10 million grant early this year.

name: William Oberndorf
desc: Oberndorf is a hedge-fund manager and Republican donor.

name: Christopher James
desc: Christopher James is a hedge-fund manager. The value of his current portfolio is in the billions.

name: Chris Larsen
desc: Chris Larsen is an angel investor and co-founder of multiple tech start-ups. In 2018, Forbes placed him as the world's fifth richest person.

name: Jason Moment
desc: Moment is managing partner of the Route One Investment Company hedge fund. He is on multiple boards around the city, including the UCSF Foundation, Benioff Children's Hospital and the Fine Arts Museums of San Francisco.

name: William F. Duhamel
desc: Duhamel is managing partner of the Route One Investment Company hedge fund.

name: Paul Holden Spaht Jr.
desc: Spaht is a Managing Partner at private equity firm Thoma Bravo. He is also on the leadership council of the anti-povery non-profit Tipping Point and Trustee of Schools of the Sacred Heart San Francisco.

name: Miriam L. Haas
desc: Haas is a billionaire businesswoman. She owns 16.7% of Levi Strauss & Co and is vice chair of the San Francisco Museum of Modern Art.
